<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How many businesses have a Google Business Profile?</strong></p>
<p>Over 200 million businesses are listed on Google Maps, with approximately 1.5 million new listings added monthly. However, only 64% of listed businesses have claimed and verified their profiles. Verified and complete profiles appear 80% more often in search results.</p>
<p><strong>What percentage of Google searches are local?</strong></p>
<p>46% of all Google searches have local intent. With Google processing an estimated 16 billion searches per day, that translates to over 7 billion local searches daily. "Near me" searches are among the fastest-growing query types.</p>
<p><strong>How many reviews does the average business need to rank?</strong></p>
<p>Top-ranking local businesses have an average of 47 <a href="/glossary/google-reviews/">Google reviews</a>. However, review velocity (frequency of new reviews) matters as much as total count. Businesses with at least 1 new review per week rank 25% higher than those with stale review profiles.</p>
<p><strong>Do Google Business Profile posts help with rankings?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Businesses posting to GBP weekly gain an average of 2.3 local pack positions over 6 months compared to businesses that do not post. Offer posts generate the highest click-through rates. See our <a href="/blog/gbp-posting-frequency/">GBP posting frequency guide</a> for a detailed schedule.</p>
<p><strong>What is the most important GBP ranking factor?</strong></p>
<p>The primary business category is the single most influential ranking factor for the local pack. GBP signals as a whole account for 32% of local pack ranking factors according to BrightLocal's 2026 study. This makes your profile more influential than your website, backlinks, and citations combined.</p>
<p><strong>How do Google reviews affect consumer decisions?</strong></p>
<p>88% of consumers read Google reviews before choosing a local business. 68% will not use a business rated below 4 stars. 73% require reviews from the last 30 days to trust a business. These numbers make active review management essential for any local business.</p>
<p>Google Business Profile is the most influential ranking factor in local search. The statistics are clear. Businesses that claim, verify, optimize, post regularly, and generate reviews win the <a href="/glossary/local-pack/">local pack</a>. Every other local SEO activity amplifies GBP signals. Start there.</p>
